:\"Good findings. So the key fact is: **`prepare-commit-msg` already fires during `git merge --squash && git commit`**, but the hook explicitly skips it (returns early for `source == \\\"squash\\\"`).\\n\\nTo answer your question:\\n\\n**Yes, it's technically possible to hook into local squash merges.** The `prepare-commit-msg` hook is called with `source=\\\"squash\\\"` when the user does `git merge --squash && git commit`. We currently skip it, but we could instead:\\n\\n1. Detect the squash scenario in `prepare-commit-msg`\\n2. Walk the commits being squashed to find all `Entire-Checkpoint` trailers\\n3. Merge the checkpoint metadata into a single new checkpoint on `entire/checkpoints/v1`\\n4. Add a single `Entire-Checkpoint` trailer to the squash commit\\n\\n**But there are real problems with this approach:**\\n\\n- **Same issue you identified** — the merged checkpoint would contain all sessions, and the user almost certainly only wants to resume the latest one. We just solved that on the resume side; doing it at merge time too would be redundant work.\\n- **The current approach already handles this well** — when someone does a local squash, all trailers survive in the commit message. Resume already picks the latest. No data is lost.\\n- **Merging metadata is lossy** — combining transcripts from different sessions into one checkpoint is messy. What does \\\"one checkpoint\\\" even mean for 3 different sessions with different prompts? Keeping them separate and picking the latest at resume time is cleaner.\\n- **Complexity for little gain** — the hook would need to parse the squashed commit range, find trailers, read metadata, merge trees, write a new checkpoint. That's a lot of code for a scenario that already works.\\n\\n**Bottom line:** The current design (preserve all trailers, resolve latest at resume time) is the right approach for both local squash merges and GitHub squash merges. Hooking into the merge to combine checkpoints would add complexity without meaningful benefit.\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1779,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":98801,\"output_tokens\":466,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":1779,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYhtkUw9Cs8DNws164DcL\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"b216e4e7-bc9b-4d33-b3ec-5c7b1c41dfb6\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T10:36:48.854Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"b216e4e7-bc9b-4d33-b3ec-5c7b1c41dfb6\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"cf32cb7d-e69d-4fde-838f-a801d52d6b92\",\"version\":\"2.1.66\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/latest-squash-resume\",\"slug\":\"purrfect-toasting-stream\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"Stop\",\"hookName\":\"Stop\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"f1c9ffae-15dd-4f0e-93cc-79a5997b39c4\",\"toolUseID\":\"f1c9ffae-15dd-4f0e-93cc-79a5997b39c4\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T10:36:48.918Z\",\"uuid\":\"3c410b85-6a59-4c00-8e44-94916f296201\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"3c410b85-6a59-4c00-8e44-94916f296201\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"cf32cb7d-e69d-4fde-838f-a801d52d6b92\",\"version\":\"2.1.66\",\"gitBranch\":\"soph/latest-squash-resume\",\"slug\":\"purrfect-toasting-stream\",\"type\":\"system\",\"subtype\":\"stop_hook_summary\",\"hookCount\":1,\"hookInfos\":[{\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\",\"durationMs\":313}],\"hookErrors\":[],\"preventedContinuation\":false,\"stopReason\":\"\",\"hasOutput\":false,\"level\":\"suggestion\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T10:36:49.231Z\",\"