oldest first). A comment noting this assumption would help future readers audit the fallback.\\n- **[resume.go:164-167]** The success message (\\\"resuming from the latest\\\") is printed even in the fallback path where selection is a heuristic. Splitting the message by outcome would be more accurate.\\n- **[resume.go:160-162]** The `resolveLatestCheckpoint` error is silently discarded. A `logging.Debug` call here would help diagnose future \\\"resumed wrong session\\\" reports.\\n- **[resume_test.go]** `TestResolveLatestCheckpoint` has no test for the error path where none of the provided IDs exist in the metadata tree.\\n\\n### Verdict: APPROVE\\n\\nThe two Important items improve clarity and context propagation, but neither is a correctness blocker for the feature itself. Estimated effort to address all feedback: ~30 minutes.\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"agentId: a89c0a9858f95dd0e (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\\n<usage>total_tokens: 72109\\ntool_uses: 15\\nduration_ms: 194225</usage>\"}]}]},\"uuid\":\"fbe4bab3-f155-4eb8-8ad8-54f1388feadf\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T10:41:18.157Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"prompt\":\"Review these changes for CODE QUALITY issues only. The diff modifies `cmd/entire/cli/resume.go`, `cmd/entire/cli/resume_test.go`, and `cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/resume_test.go`.\\n\\nHere's the new code in resume.go:\\n\\n```go\\ncheckpointID := result.checkpointIDs[0]\\n\\n// Multiple checkpoints (squash merge): resolve latest and resume from it\\nif len(result.checkpointIDs) > 1 {\\n    latest, err := resolveLatestCheckpoint(repo, result.checkpointIDs)\\n    if err != nil {\\n        // Fallback: use last trailer\\n        latest = result.checkpointIDs[len(result.checkpointIDs)-1]\\n    }\\n    skipped := len(result.checkpointIDs) - 1\\n    fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \\\"Found %d checkpoints on the latest commit in this branch, resuming from the latest (%d older checkpoints skipped)\\\\n\\\",\\n  